Sunny- wind northeast at 5 mph- very little bloom- and the temperature is 87 degrees F.
Sunny but hazy- ripple on water- and southwest wind at 5-7 mph.
Cloudy and sunshine- ripple on water- and 5 mph southeast wind.
Sunny but overcast.  Water level: very low-22"
Partially sunny- last report for the season.  Water level: very low (20")
Bright and sunny- breezy.  Water level: very low.
Weeds in the littoral zone greater than
Brisk breeze- bright and sunny- no rain all spring- 3 mature eagles over lake.  Water level: very low.
Brisk breeze- bright- sunny.  Water level: very low.
Opinion affected by big boats and motors- overcast- slight breeze/ripples.  Water level: very low.

Careless boaters.  Water level: very low.
No water in channel or on sand bars- boating limited.  Water level: very low.
Less boating and water skiing since channel is so low.
Can't get through channel to alma lake
Sunny- few boats since channel can't be navigated
Boating down 50% since channel to alma lake too low
Bar in E bay so low no large boats can cross
Water low- grassy areas in E bay.
Aquatic vegetation. showing more than usual due to low water
Eagles- osprey and gulls enjoying low water for food supply
Lake very clear- jet skis causing concern for residents.  Lake level: still 30" low
Eagle and osprey bathe in lake on shallow sand bar regularly
Partly sunny- little algae this year- level up 10"- loons with 2 chicks.  Water level: up but low
Mostly cloudy- ducks leaving- loons still here.  Lake level: still low- up 10"
Pollen on water- little boat traffic- loons returned 4/15. Water level: 18" higher
Sunny- pan fishing picked up- several new cottages built. Water level: 18" higher
Sunny- heavy lake traffic- loon pair
Sunny- traffic picking up- eagles- osprey

Sunny- clear- calm- some boat traffic.- Assumed time was 12:00.
Cool- sunny- breezy- water is slightly rough.

Lots of rain.  Lake level: very high
Some pollen seen on water near shore.
Heavy boat usage- no clouds- NW light wind.
No boat traffic- no wind- no clouds- clear skies.
Partly cloudy- SW wind- no boat traffic.
Very minor-too cold to swim.  Minor clouds- SW wind- minor wave action (no white caps) - no boat traffic.
Northwest wind. ice out May 12- 96. partly  to mostly cloudy. waves (no whitecaps) .
Northwest wind. partly cloudy. heavy heavy boat traffic last 3 days.
Northwest wind- partly cloudy- boat traffic light.
Light to no wind. partly cloudy. boat traffic light.
Southwest light wind- partly cloudy- temp. 58 degrees F.

WSW wind- sunny- few high clouds.
Light n. wind.  Sunny.  High clouds.

Very light wind. puffy clouds. sun. low boat traffic

Fourth of July!  Sunny and calm.
